        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[From a shrine pond to a Mirpur flat: We keep mourning what we fail to protect]]></title>
            <description><![CDATA[Instead of framing the issue as a debate on tradition versus modernity, we need to ask whether we are capable of caring for what we claim to value. If the crocodile was heritage, why was it not managed responsibly? If the child’s safety mattered, why was the danger not addressed earlier? If the shrine was sacred, why was its ecology left to improvisation?]]></description>
            <link>https://www.thedailystar.net/opinion/views/blowin-the-wind/news/shrine-pond-mirpur-flat-we-keep-mourning-what-we-fail-protect-4191486</link>
